+# Human Bubble Replies Manual / Simulated Validation
+
+Date: 2026-05-03
+Branch: feature/human-bubble-replies
+
+## Environment
+
+- Source worktree: `/root/.openclaw/repos/openclaw/.worktrees/human-bubble-replies`
+- Runtime gateway was not modified during simulated validation.
+- Validation mode: local tests and code-path simulation only.
+
+## Simulated tests run
+
+```bash
+corepack pnpm test -- \
+  src/auto-reply/reply/human-bubble-markers.test.ts \
+  src/auto-reply/reply/block-reply-pipeline.test.ts \
+  src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.human-bubble-block-reply.test.ts
+```
+
+Expected:
+
+- Parser strips and validates markers.
+- Telegram DM scope emits three block replies for two markers.
+- Unsupported scope strips markers and emits one cleaned block reply.
+- Per-bubble delay is honored by block reply pipeline.
+- Final dedupe ignores bubble markers.
+
+Actual:
+
+- PASS: `human-bubble-markers.test.ts` — 10 tests.
+- PASS: `block-reply-pipeline.test.ts` — 17 tests.
+- PASS: `pi-embedded-subscribe.human-bubble-block-reply.test.ts` — 2 tests.
+
+## Manual Telegram test not yet run
+
+The current live OpenClaw runtime under `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw` was not replaced with this worktree build. No live Telegram message was sent as part of this validation.
+
+## Risk notes
+
+- This feature modifies OpenClaw core block-reply delivery, so it is more central than a standalone plugin.
+- It does not bypass channel delivery and does not call Telegram Bot API directly.
+- The main safety properties are covered by tests: marker stripping, scope gating, per-bubble delay, and final dedupe.
